<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-454-454  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 454 454.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  May 21 1990 v24 n21 p68(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC price caps proposal under fire. (Federal CommunicationsCommission plans to extend price caps to local telephonecompanies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anthes, Gary H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Telecommunications users and trade associations oppose a proposalby the Federal Communications Commission to extend the price capsthe FCC places on ATandamp;T to local telephone companies.andP;  Critics saythe proposal, under which fixed price limits would replace theolder 'rate of return' concept, would lead to higher prices andpoor service.andP;  The software trade organization Adapso says thatprice caps for local exchange carriers are inappropriate becausethe local firms, unlike ATandamp;T, enjoy monopoly power and couldunlawfully shift costs from unregulated lines of business toregulated ones.andP;  FCC officials have proposed to bracket localexchange carrier profits within a 'zone of reasonableness.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone companiesUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationPricing PolicyPolitical IssuesGovernment Agency.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>